com.viaoa.hub

Class HubGroupBy<F extends OAObject,G extends OAObject>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.viaoa.hub.HubGroupBy<F,G>

  • public class HubGroupBy<F extends OAObject,G extends OAObject>
extends java.lang.Object
    Combines a hub into a new single hub to create the equivalent of a database groupBy. The combined Hub (see getCombinedHub) uses OAObject OAGroupBy, where G is the same class as the groupBy Hub and F is a hub of the from objects. // group Employees by Dept new HubGroupBy(hubEmp, hubAllDept, "depts") new HubGroupBy(hubEmp, "depts") Split property path - this is when all of the methods in a pp are not public (link that does not create method). HubGroupBy is able to group them by splitting the pp using HubGroupBy and HubFrom to get a combined group. ex: MRADClient.Application.ApplicationType.ApplicationGroup, hubFrom=hubMRADClients, hubGroupBy=hubApplicationGroups note: the method for ApplicationType.getApplicationGroups() is not created (is private) new HubGroupBy(hubMRADClients, hubApplicationGroups, "MRADClient.Application.ApplicationType.ApplicationGroup") internally will create 2 HubGroupBys ... (hubMRADClients, "MRADClient.Application.ApplicationType") (hubApplicationGroups, "ApplicationTypes")
    Author:
    vvia
    See Also:
    to create a "flat" list., type of object for combined

      • HubGroupBy

        public HubGroupBy(Hub<F> hubB,
          Hub<G> hubFrom,
          java.lang.String propertyPath,
          boolean bCreateNullList)
        Create a hub on objects that are based on hubB, and are grouped by hubA. This allows a the combined hub to have a full list like a left-join.
        Parameters:
        hubA - objects that are to be grouped.
        hubB - optional list of objects to have as the master list. This will act as a left-join
        propertyPath - pp of the property from the right object to get left object. example: if hubDept, hubEmpOrders, then "Employee.Department" HubGroupBy(hubEmpOrders, hubDept, "Employee.Department") -or- HubGroupBy(hubEmpOrders, "Employee.Department")
